{"id":14881510,"mediaExerciseId":"6d832f9c-2524-48be-99c0-15c940bc7224","exerciseName":"8","chapterName":"15","chapterTitle":"Raising Capital","groupId":612403,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":529,"solutions":[{"id":6025083,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"We are asked to assess the cash offer and rights offer in this exercise. \n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":28,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/7bd4a60333cc9cb1e53a9ff9ee66a980/c71d54b5b9efdc396fb5f753523d8ed7/lateximg_large.png","width":911},"regular":{"height":15,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/7bd4a60333cc9cb1e53a9ff9ee66a980/c71d54b5b9efdc396fb5f753523d8ed7/lateximg.png","width":457}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"The **right offering** is a public offering of shares in which existing shareholders are initially given securities. There is no additional stock issued in a rights issue, lowering a present company's ownership proportion as long as the existing shareholder exercises all of his rights to maintain an equal proportion shareholding by subscribing to new share financings at or below market rates. \n\nIn a **cash offer**, the additional stock is offered to outside shareholders, diluting the existing ownership. This is a public offering of securities for cash sale to the public.\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":331,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/7bd4a60333cc9cb1e53a9ff9ee66a980/acb57562d8fcddf19b54ce9204d61854/lateximg_large.png","width":1042},"regular":{"height":166,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/7bd4a60333cc9cb1e53a9ff9ee66a980/acb57562d8fcddf19b54ce9204d61854/lateximg.png","width":522}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"The firm prefers a cheaper alternative between a cash offer and a rights offering since it is interested in lowering selling expenses.\n\n**If the firm is looking for a less expensive option, it is advisable to go with a rights offering.** This safeguards current stockholders' proportional interests and prevents underpricing. This is also the most cost-effective way for the firm to raise funds. Stockholders are given preference by providing more firm securities at a lower price than the market price.\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":254,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/7bd4a60333cc9cb1e53a9ff9ee66a980/ed794daa8cb32e0b53cf961729756004/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":128,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/7bd4a60333cc9cb1e53a9ff9ee66a980/ed794daa8cb32e0b53cf961729756004/lateximg.png","width":499}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"**To conclude, the firm should consider a rights offer over a cash offer since it is significantly less expensive. However, there may be additional expenses associated with taking advantage of such an offer.**","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":105,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/7bd4a60333cc9cb1e53a9ff9ee66a980/34c14ca4d2beaa8d2429c4406c875bc7/lateximg_large.png","width":995},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/15/7bd4a60333cc9cb1e53a9ff9ee66a980/34c14ca4d2beaa8d2429c4406c875bc7/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4}],"rating":0,"solutionUuid":"2ad0ad76-3e8b-485f-908f-ddee850f6e37","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":4}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881511,"exerciseName":"9","page":529,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"f138bb53-cb83-44e3-8503-aafb796e590d","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-15-critical-thinking-questions-9-f138bb53-cb83-44e3-8503-aafb796e590d"},{"id":14881512,"exerciseName":"10","page":530,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"8f4bd1f9-c91c-4b0b-ab08-648d3f9aad46","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-15-critical-thinking-questions-10-8f4bd1f9-c91c-4b0b-ab08-648d3f9aad46"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14881509,"exerciseName":"7","page":529,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"bf794185-7860-4957-96df-d0d5348ef477","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-15-critical-thinking-questions-7-bf794185-7860-4957-96df-d0d5348ef477"},{"id":14881508,"exerciseName":"6","page":529,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"443a32bd-7267-4cd4-a597-04073a50feb2","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-15-critical-thinking-questions-6-443a32bd-7267-4cd4-a597-04073a50feb2"}],"_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-15-critical-thinking-questions-8-6d832